        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test(auto-reply): add unit tests for ACP reset target session key resolution",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe `acp-reset-target.ts` module resolves ACP reset targets from sessions and command directives, coordinating service bindings, configured bindings, and raw ACP binding fallback. Despite being a core path in auto-reply reset target resolution, this module had no unit tests to verify the resolution logic.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd unit tests for `resolveEffectiveResetTargetSessionKey` to verify:\n- Input normalization edge cases (missing channel/conversationId, empty strings, non-ACP active sessions)\n- Service binding resolution (ACP key recognition, non-ACP filtering, whitespace trimming, empty-after-trim)\n- Priority chain: service binding takes precedence over active session\n- `skipConfiguredFallbackWhenActiveSessionNonAcp` flag behavior (skip vs continue)\n- Configured binding resolution with `allowNonAcpBindingSessionKey` flag\n- Raw configured ACP session key fallback from bindings list\n- `fallbackToActiveAcpWhenUnbound` default/disabled behavior\n- accountId resolution from channel `defaultAccount` config\n\nThis improves test coverage and prevents regressions when the function is modified.\n\n## User Impact\n\nACP reset target resolution now has dedicated unit coverage, reducing the risk of regressions when the function is modified.\n\n## Evidence\n\nReproducibility: not applicable. This PR adds direct coverage for existing helper behavior rather than reporting a user-visible runtime bug. Source inspection confirms the helper behavior the tests target.\n\nDirect behavior probe (no mocks — real function exercised through default dependencies):\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx -e \"import('./src/auto-reply/reply/acp-reset-target.js').then(({ resolveEffectiveResetTargetSessionKey }) => { const cfg = { channels: {}, bindings: [] }; const results = []; results.push({ desc: 'no channel/conversationId returns undefined', result: resolveEffectiveResetTargetSessionKey({ cfg }) }); results.push({ desc: 'active ACP session preserved without channel', result: resolveEffectiveResetTargetSessionKey({ cfg, activeSessionKey: 'acp:real-session' }), expected: 'acp:real-session' }); results.push({ desc: 'non-ACP active session returns undefined without channel', result: resolveEffectiveResetTargetSessionKey({ cfg, activeSessionKey: 'non-acp' }) }); results.push({ desc: 'fallbackToActiveAcpWhenUnbound=false blocks fallback', result: resolveEffectiveResetTargetSessionKey({ cfg, channel: 'test', conversationId: 'test-c', activeSessionKey: 'acp:test', fallbackToActiveAcpWhenUnbound: false }) }); console.log(JSON.stringify(results, null, 2)); })\"\n[\n  {\n    \"desc\": \"no channel/conversationId returns undefined\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"desc\": \"active ACP session preserved without channel\",\n    \"result\": \"acp:real-session\",\n    \"expected\": \"acp:real-session\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"desc\": \"non-ACP active session returns undefined without channel\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"desc\": \"fallbackToActiveAcpWhenUnbound=false blocks fallback\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nTargeted test:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/auto-reply/reply/acp-reset-target.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  25 passed (25)\n   Start at  23:48:24\n   Duration  2.49s (transform 997ms, setup 0ms, import 2.25s, tests 17ms, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 14.36s\n```\n\nFormatting:\n\n```text\n$ npx oxfmt --check src/auto-reply/reply/acp-reset-target.ts src/auto-reply/reply/acp-reset-target.test.ts\nChecking formatting...\n\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\nWhitespace:\n\n```text\n$ git diff --check\n```\n\n## AI-assisted\n\nPrepared with Codex. I reviewed the change, understand the touched code path, and kept the PR focused on the test coverage described above.",
